text: Hypatima venefica is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Ponomarenko in 1991. It is found in the Russian Far East, Korea and Japan.Hypatima at funetJapanese Moths The wingspan is 14.5–19 mm. The forewings are ochreous, speckled with light brown scales and dark fuscous streaks near the base, the middle and beneath and beyond the cell. The hindwings are grey.Insecta koreana 10 : 34 The larvae feed on Quercus mongolica. ==References== Category:Hypatima Category:Moths described in 1991
